	order_index: 12
	quest_links: [ ]
	quests: [
		{
			description: [
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Draconic Codex</grad>"
				"A codex, what is a mod without its boring guidebook."
				"The difference is though, this one is not really boring and has plenty of features!"
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Once you open it, on the right</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>you'll see colorful pins:</grad>"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FF0000 to=#FF6666 f=0.5>Red</grad> is information about your tamed dragon:"
				"[gap=0]"
				"Health, Armor, Gender, Happiness, Hunger, etc."
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#63B3FF to=#B8E0FF f=0.5>Blue</grad> is the Ecology Tab, showing information about a clicked dragon."
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FF6A00 to=#FFB347 f=0.5>Orange</grad> is a player whitelist."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>To view anything in them, right-click a dragon with the codex.</grad>"
			]
			id: "4BDE217F95FD62A2"
			min_width: 240
			rewards: [{
				id: "305E928549386662"
				item: "saintsdragons:mossback"
				type: "item"
			}]
			shape: "hexagon"
			size: 1.3d
			subtitle: "<typewriter><shadow><grad from=#FFE44D to=#FFFFB3 f=0.3>Fat mossback as a reward!</grad></shadow>"
			tasks: [{
				id: "2334155A8A8B61F0"
				item: "saintsdragons:draconic_codex"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "<shadow><grad from=#FFE44D to=#FFFFB3 f=0.5><wave a=0.5 f=0.8 w=0.5>Draconic Codex</wave></grad></shadow>"
			x: 2.0d
			y: -3.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["4BDE217F95FD62A2"]
			description: [
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Overview</grad>"
				"The <grad from=#8B0000 to=#C0392B f=1>Raevyx</grad> is a rare, combat-oriented dragon species known for its nomadic behavior, aerial agility, and calculated aggression."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Their egg can be found in structures:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&7Villager Outposts&r and &3Ancient Cities&r,"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>They can be found in the following biomes:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&2Plains&r, &2Meadow&r, &eSunflower Plains&r, etc.."
				"[gap=0]"
				"during a thunderstorm with a rare chance."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to look how to tame them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Taming</grad>"
				"&6Required food&r"
				"Raw Cod, Raw Salmon, Hearty Dragon Meal."
				"Just feeding him won't be so easy, first you need to lower his health to &c60&r, and then feed him any of the food, it's also not guranteed to tame him first time, if you fail to tame him, you'd have to lower his health again."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view how to breed them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Breeding</grad>"
				"Requires a pair of one male and one female with full health. Shift + Right-click with the appropriate food item under the Taming section to initiate breeding. Should you breed one male dragon that you own with a female dragon that someone else owns, or otherwise, the baby will default to following the female."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view their abilities.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Keys - Abilities</grad>"
				"[gap=5]"
				"&2Left-click&r - Bite with chain lightning."
				"&2X&r - to switch to Horn Goring."
				"&2R&r - Roar: summons &f2&r to &f5&r lightning bolts if an enemy aggro onto it/its owner."
				"&2G&r - Beaming: Hold to shoot a devastating beam of lightning."
				"&2H&r - Storm Summoning: Stats doubled."
				"[gap=0]"
				"Sky changes. &f1&r-minute usage, &f5&r-minute cooldown."
				"&2Holding H&r on the ground - Ground Rending."
				"&2Double-tapping&r &2A&r, &2S&r, and &2D&r to dodge left, back, and right."
				"&2Double-tapping W&r will make it dash forward, dealing damage on the ground. Can only dodge in the air. "
			]
			id: "5D3B8B73B02315AC"
			min_width: 250
			shape: "none"
			size: 1.1d
			subtitle: "<typewriter><shadow><grad from=#C0392B to=#E8614F f=0.3>For some reason, he re-e-eally hates cockroaches.</grad></shadow>"
			tasks: [{
				id: "0D7AC702B13D647B"
				item: "saintsdragons:raevyx_egg"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "<shadow><grad from=#C0392B to=#E8614F f=1><wave a=0.5 f=0.8 w=0.5>Raevyx</wave></grad></shadow>"
			x: 2.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["4BDE217F95FD62A2"]
			description: [
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Overview</grad>"
				"The <grad from=#4A4646 to=#B5A8A8 f=1>Ignivorus</grad> is a colossal fire-adapted dragon species known for its overwhelming physical presence and extreme thermal output."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Their egg can be found in structures:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&bAncient City&r, &6Nether Fortress&r, &8Bastion Remnant&r."
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>They can be found in the following biomes:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&2Plains&r, &2Meadow&r, &7Windswept Hills&r, etc.."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to look how to tame them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Taming</grad>"
				"&6Required food&r"
				"Raw Cod, Raw Salmon, Raw Beef,"
				"[gap=0]"
				"Hearty Dragon Meal."
				"Just feeding him won't be so easy, first you need to lower his health to &c100&r, and then feed him any of the food, it's also not guranteed to tame him first time, if you fail to tame him, you'd have to lower his health again."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view how to breed them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Breeding</grad>"
				"Requires a pair of one male and one female with full health. Shift + Right-click with the appropriate food item under the Taming section to initiate breeding. Should you breed one male dragon that you own with a female dragon that someone else owns, or otherwise, the baby will default to following the female."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view their abilities.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Keys - Abilities</grad>"
				"To activate &2Phase 2&r once you've tamed one, &2double-tap&r the &2S&r key."
				"&ePhase 1&r: Left-click: Bite that sets targets of fire."
				"&2X&r to switch to Body Slam"
				"&ePhase 2&r: Left-click: Wing slap."
				"&2X&r to switch to Stomp."
				"&2R&r - Roar: Summons three magma pillars three times on the ground. &2Hold R&r to charge up a 3-level fireball. The bigger the level, the stronger the fireball."
				"&ePhase 1 and 2&r: &2G&r - Fire Breathing: &2Hold&r to shoot a stream of fire. &2Hold&r a little longer to destroy blocks."
				"&2H&r - Supernova (exaggerated): Releases a big explosion. Nearby mobs get decimated at the cost of health. Phase 2 happens in an instant, no wind-up."
				"&ePhase 1&r: &2Double-tapping W&r will make Ignivorus enter its bulldozing state. &2Double-tapping&r again to exit."
				"&ePhase 2&r: &2Double-tapping W&r will make Ignivorus do a leaping body slam."
				"## Damn."
			]
			id: "2831BA1070C5D09F"
			min_width: 250
			shape: "none"
			size: 1.1d
			subtitle: "<typewriter><shadow><grad from=#4A4646 to=#B5A8A8 f=0.3>Aura farming dragon.</grad></shadow>"
			tasks: [{
				id: "59AF2A8DC9BFCB6E"
				item: "saintsdragons:ignivorus_egg"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "<shadow><grad from=#4A4646 to=#B5A8A8 f=1><wave a=0.5 f=0.8 w=0.5>Ignivorus</wave></grad></shadow>"
			x: -5.0d
			y: -5.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["4BDE217F95FD62A2"]
			description: [
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Overview</grad>"
				"The <grad from=#228B22 to=#AAFF00 f=1>Varasuchus</grad> is a highly adaptive semi-aquatic dragon species known for its phase-shifting combat behavior and deceptive threat presentation."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Their egg can be found in biomes:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&6Beach&r, &7Stony Shore&r."
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>They can be found in the following biomes:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&6Beach&r, &bSnowy Beach&r, &bStony Shores&r."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to look how to tame them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Taming</grad>"
				"These ones are a bit different, you gotta ride them and remain on top for some amount of time for them to be tamed."
				"&eBabies are fed with:&r"
				"Raw Cod, Raw Salmon, Tropical Fish, Hearty Dragon Meal."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view how to breed them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Breeding</grad>"
				"Requires a pair of one male and one female with full health. Shift + Right-click with the appropriate food item under the Taming section to initiate breeding. Should you breed one male dragon that you own with a female dragon that someone else owns, or otherwise, the baby will default to following the female."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view their abilities.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Keys - Abilities</grad>"
				"&eThis dragon has the ability to jump like vanilla Horses.&r"
				"&2Left-click&r: Bite."
				"&2X&r to switch to Horn Goring."
				"&2Hold R&r only on &ePhase 1&r: Tail guard and parry. While holding, Varasuchus will enter a guarding stance, immune to damage. If something attacks it while in guard, it'll perform a parry and knocks everything back while dealing damage."
				"&2R&r - On &ePhase 2&r: Unleashes a slash barrage."
				"&2G&r - Tail attack on phase 1. Clawing on phase 2."
				"&2H&r - Phase Shifting: Phase 2. Stops playing nice. Go from quadruped to bipedal."
				"&2Double-tap W&r for a dash and tail swiping in &ephase 1&r, and a dash and clawing in &ephase 2&r."
			]
			id: "13917F283F0419B3"
			min_width: 250
			shape: "none"
			size: 1.1d
			subtitle: "<typewriter><shadow><grad from=#32CD32 to=#CCFF66 f=0.3>Wait.. he kinda looks like a cockroach..</grad></shadow>"
			tasks: [{
				id: "45B967088CA9259C"
				item: "saintsdragons:varasuchus_egg"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "<grad from=#32CD32 to=#CCFF66 f=1><wave a=0.5 f=0.8 w=0.5>Varasuchus</wave></grad>"
			x: -5.0d
			y: -1.0d
		}
		{
			dependencies: ["4BDE217F95FD62A2"]
			description: [
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Overview</grad>"
				"The <grad from=#FF6A00 to=#4A5E23 f=1>Cindervane</grad> is a highly migratory draconic species known for its exceptional endurance and long-distance flight capability."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Their egg can be found in biomes:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&2Plains biome&r."
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>They can be found in the following biomes:</grad>"
				"[gap=0]"
				"&2Meadow&r, &bFrozen Peaks&r, &bSnowy Slopes&r, etc.."
				"[gap=5]"
				"---"
				"[gap=5]"
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to look how to tame them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Taming</grad>"
				"&6Required food&r"
				"Raw Cod, Raw Salmon, Raw Chicken, Hearty Dragon Meal."
				"May require multiple attempts to tame."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view how to breed them.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Breeding</grad>"
				"Requires a pair of one male and one female with full health. Shift + Right-click with the appropriate food item under the Taming section to initiate breeding. Should you breed one male dragon that you own with a female dragon that someone else owns, or otherwise, the baby will default to following the female."
				"<grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Go to the next page to view their abilities.</grad>"
				"{@pagebreak}"
				"## <grad from=#FFD700 to=#FFFF99 f=0.5>Keys - Abilities</grad>"
				"&2Left-click&r - Bite. "
				"&2X&r - to switch to slash-grab."
				"&2R&r - Roar: Purely cosmetic."
				"&2G&r - Ignition: Sets itself on fire."
				"Diving down from the air while on fire"
				"[gap=0]"
				"causes a massive explosion"
				"&2H&r - Magma Volley: Spits out three magma cubes three times. "
			]
